<br>
If you have the 61 pet you can aggro kite ravens, spiders, and trees in PoN by pulling with FoT and nuking at every chance with another. Mana intensive and not great solo xp.<br>
<br>
I wouldn't say that soloing in the planes are worthwhile, and a pally partner with a mage isn't a lot of help, unless he can land a few stuns to help mitigate some damage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nanid>Nanid</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.scorpz.com/icq.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 130<br> <font color=#333333>(2/18/03 12:46:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=54.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.scorpz.com/nanidezz.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tier 1 solo spots?</span><hr size=1> For tier one... dun think there's much for a 61 mage to solo for good xp... at least IMO. <br>
<br>
