<br>
The mob will be pulled with malosini. I will lead off the fight by chaining BO 5'ed air pets until my mana drops below half.    Once mana gets below half, I start reclaim chaining unbuffed (GVoc) earth pets as a method of regaining mana quickly while still fighting.  The situation I'm looking for is the earth pet casting root twice within a 10 second period, pretty much assuring one of the two roots held. This typically happens very early after the pet first engages.  As soon as it casts the second root, reclaim and recast.  Do this until back up above 75% mana, then go back to chaining 61 air pets.  Finish the fight with the air pet and a nuke.<br>
<br>
I have been able to successfully solo these mobs using this approach. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jochangaladar>Jochan Galadar</A> at: 2/18/03 3:12:53 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thedwellerindarkness@themagicianstower>thedwellerindarkness</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 460<br> <font color=#333333>(2/18/03 4:29:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=54.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tier 1 solo spots?</span><hr size=1> That technique sounds like it would take quite a while. Why not simply nuke full speed (yes you'll end up with aggro and be aggro kiting a bit), then reclaim pets for mana at the end of the fight? Seems like over all that would be faster.<br>
<br>
I agree the soloing in PoP is not worthwhile for us. Duos, however, are very worthwhile and fun. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hgishbu>HG Ishbu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#333333>(2/18/03 4:43:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=54.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tier 1 solo spots?</span><hr size=1> goo's in PoD are soloable if there is no other option for exp...when i do them pet usualy ends up at around 50health and i have like 60mana left <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ailees>Ailees</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ikebana-toulouse.com/maitres/ailees.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 878<br> <font color=#333333>(2/18/03 9:12:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=54.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.ikebana-toulouse.com/citation/tov.jpg WIDTH=120 HEIGHT=160></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tier 1 solo spots?</span><hr size=1> at 61/62 I soloed at POD with EPIC pet buffed, he rocks better than 61 for soloing and tanking. Weapons and belt if possible.<br>
